# Multilingual drum instrument name → Paradiddle MIDI note lookup
# Used by the Sheet Music → MIDI converter to correct wrong note numbers
# in MusicXML files based on the human-readable instrument-name string.
# Covers MuseScore localizations: English, French, German, Spanish,
# Italian, Portuguese, Dutch, Polish, Russian (transliterated), Japanese
# (transliterated), and Classical/formal Latin-root terms.
# Longest match wins — more specific terms (e.g. "crash cymbal 1") always
# beat shorter ones (e.g. "crash") so order within the dict doesn't matter.
