        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.5\n"
              "  Bug Fixes:\n"
              "  - The Detection Engine's \"↓ Get Model\" button is fixed.\n"
              "    Previously the button tried to download the AI drum model\n"
              "    from the wrong web address, so it always failed and showed\n"
              "    \"Download failed from all sources.\" The button now reaches\n"
              "    the correct GitHub release on the first try.\n"
              "  - Get / Download Model buttons now gray out automatically once\n"
              "    the model is on your computer. Before, every Download button\n"
              "    stayed clickable even when the file was already downloaded,\n"
              "    which was confusing and could trigger redundant downloads.\n"
              "    This now applies to the Detection Engine model, the Stem\n"
              "    Splitter (DrumSep) model, and the v4.4.4 Neural Stem\n"
              "    Isolation model — all three behave consistently.\n"
              "  - No charts or settings are affected; this is a UI fix only.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.4\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - Neural Stem Isolation (experimental, opt-in). New section in\n"
              "    the Audio → MIDI Settings panel: \"Neural Stem Isolation\".\n"
              "    Off by default; flip the radio to Jarredou MDX23C and ParaKit\n"
              "    will run your audio through an AI splitter before detection,\n"
              "    cleaning up bleed between kick / snare / hi-hat / toms /\n"
              "    cymbals. Detection then runs on the cleaned audio.\n"
              "  - Why: on tricky tracks (especially metal) where drums bleed\n"
              "    into each other, the splitter can dramatically reduce the\n"
              "    amount of editor cleanup. Internal testing on a 5-track metal\n"
              "    corpus showed strong improvements on snare, kick, and crash\n"
              "    detection vs. default detection.\n"
              "  - First-time setup: ~417 MB one-time model download (the model\n"
              "    is not bundled because its upstream license is unspecified).\n"
              "    Click \"↓ Download model\" in the Settings section and ParaKit\n"
              "    will fetch and verify it. Saved to your user app-data folder.\n"
              "  - Cost / caveats: adds ~30-60s per song on CPU. GPU not yet\n"
              "    supported in this version. The ride lane still uses default\n"
              "    detection. If anything goes wrong with the splitter at run\n"
              "    time, ParaKit falls back to default detection so your\n"
              "    conversion still finishes.\n"
              "  - Architecture note: this is the first plug-in for ParaKit's\n"
              "    new separator-slot system. Future research-validated drum\n"
              "    splitters can plug into the same slot when their license\n"
              "    permits and their accuracy matches.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.3\n"
              "  Bug Fixes:\n"
              "  - Kick detection cleanup. The detector sometimes fired multiple\n"
              "    kick onsets very close together (under 30ms) for what was\n"
              "    actually a single kick hit, leaving you with clusters of\n"
              "    duplicate kick notes to clean up in the editor. The kick-\n"
              "    dedup window has been widened to 40ms (up from 30ms in\n"
              "    spectral mode and 20ms in hybrid mode) so those near-\n"
              "    duplicate triggers get merged into one kick automatically.\n"
              "    Validated against a 5-track metal corpus: detection accuracy\n"
              "    improves on every track, and legitimate fast double-kicks\n"
              "    (16th-note rolls at metal tempos) are not affected — real\n"
              "    fast kicks are spaced wider than 40ms.\n"
              "  - If you noticed cluster-style kick notes in your charts\n"
              "    (especially on metal/heavy material), this should reduce them\n"
              "    substantially. No action needed on existing charts; just\n"
              "    convert again if you want the cleaner result.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.2\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - YouTube → FLAC: optional custom filename. New checkbox\n"
              "    \"Name file other than video title\" — when checked, you\n"
              "    get a text field to type your own filename. The file\n"
              "    extension (.flac, .mp3, etc.) is added automatically based\n"
              "    on the format you chose; you just type the name.\n"
              "  - Why: sometimes a YouTube title has too much extra info\n"
              "    (\"[Official 4K Music Video] (Audio Remastered) - ARTIST -\n"
              "    SONG (2024)\") or not enough (\"audio_001\"). Now you control it.\n"
              "  - Windows file-name rules are auto-enforced — invalid\n"
              "    characters like < > : \" / \\ | ? * get replaced with\n"
              "    underscores so saves never fail. A live preview below\n"
              "    the text field shows exactly how your file will be named\n"
              "    before you click download.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.1\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - Enhanced Detection got more flexible. Instead of one on/off\n"
              "    toggle, you now pick what kind of enhancement you want: Off\n"
              "    (default detection), Crash only, Toms only, or Crash + Toms\n"
              "    (the v4.4.0 default).\n"
              "  - Why: some songs benefit from better crash pickup but do not\n"
              "    need extra tom help. Crash only avoids unwanted tom notes on\n"
              "    songs that do not have any toms. Rock and metal tracks with\n"
              "    big fills may benefit from both.\n"
              "  - Existing v4.4.0 settings carry over: if Enhanced Detection\n"
              "    was ON, you are now set to Crash + Toms automatically. If it\n"
              "    was OFF, you are still OFF.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.4.0\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - Better tom detection on tracks with prominent tom fills\n"
              "    (rock, metal, jazz). When Enhanced Detection is ON, ParaKit\n"
              "    now uses an extra processing step that picks up tom hits the\n"
              "    main detector tends to miss. Internal testing showed roughly\n"
              "    3.5x more correctly-detected tom hits on tracks where the\n"
              "    main detector was struggling.\n"
              "  - Heads up on tom-sparse material: on tracks with very few or\n"
              "    zero tom hits (some pop, electronic, ballads), the new\n"
              "    processing step can occasionally add unwanted tom notes that\n"
              "    aren't in the original recording. If you see these after\n"
              "    detection, drag-select across the tom row in the MIDI Editor\n"
              "    and press Delete to clean up. This trade-off was accepted in\n"
              "    exchange for catching many more real tom hits on tom-prominent\n"
              "    material.\n"
              "  - This change is gated behind the existing \"Enhanced Detection\"\n"
              "    toggle; if you keep that off, the new processing doesn't run\n"
              "    and detection behaves exactly as it did in v4.3.30.\n")

        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.3.30\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - Snare detection is now better at telling real snare hits apart\n"
              "    from kick rebounds and tom bleed. The wire-band check (the part\n"
              "    that listens for the metallic snare-wire sizzle on top of the\n"
              "    drum body) is now stricter, so onsets that look like a snare in\n"
              "    the body band but lack the wire signature get rejected.\n"
              "  - Validated against an 18-track tuning set plus an 8-track edge-\n"
              "    case set covering pop, metal, rock, and alternative material.\n"
              "    97% of the events the new threshold drops are false positives;\n"
              "    only 3% are real snare hits, and those losses are spread thin\n"
              "    enough that no track measurably loses real snare hits.\n"
              "    Net effect: cleaner snare lanes, fewer ghost\n"
              "    onsets that need scrubbing in the MIDI Editor.\n"
              "  - The Funk preset's snare sensitivity stays where it was (slightly\n"
              "    looser, on purpose, for ghost notes). Only the default snare\n"
              "    setting got tightened.\n")

