        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.2.13\n"
              "  Changes/Additions:\n"
              "  - MIDI Editor: Reactive Notes toggle (Display & Snap panel). When on,\n"
              "    notes flash solid white as the playhead passes over them (+/-40 ms\n"
              "    window). Works during playback, scrubbing, and while paused. Useful\n"
              "    for checking note placement in tricky sections. Toggle off anytime\n"
              "    to return to normal colors.\n"
              "  - Song Creator / Batch: Pre-flight button renamed to 'Check for Issues'\n"
              "    across all tabs for clarity. Behavior is unchanged.\n"
              "  Bug Fixes:\n"
              "  - MIDI Extractor (.rlrr -> MIDI): fixed a drift bug where the output\n"
              "    MIDI's note timings drifted from the source .rlrr by roughly 125 ms\n"
              "    per simultaneous-event pair, accumulating to multi-second drift by\n"
              "    the end of a song with dense patterns. Sparse charts with no\n"
              "    overlapping hits were unaffected; dense charts (kick+hihat patterns,\n"
              "    cymbal-on-snare, fast rolls, etc.) could produce MIDIs that no\n"
              "    longer lined up with the audio when re-imported.\n"
              "  - Affects the standalone MIDI Extractor menu item (Audio to MIDI menu\n"
              "    and Tools menu) and the metadata-preserving 'Save MIDI with title'\n"
              "    variant. Both now group simultaneous events at the same absolute\n"
              "    tick and use a 1-tick note duration so a note's release no longer\n"
              "    blocks the next note's start.\n"
              "  - Verified post-fix max timing drift is <=0.52 ms across long dense\n"
              "    songs (down from multi-second on the worst cases). For drum data,\n"
              "    note durations are decorative -- only note-on times matter for\n"
              "    audio alignment.")

