        wn_entry(wn_older,
              "v4.2.10\n"
              "  Bug Fixes:\n"
              "  - MIDI Editor: hotkeys now resume working after typing in any text\n"
              "    field. Previously, once you clicked into the Note offset, BPM, or\n"
              "    audio path field the canvas lost keyboard focus and 1-8 lane keys,\n"
              "    Ctrl+Z/C/V, Delete, and others stopped responding. Reclaiming focus\n"
              "    required clicking the editor canvas in specific ways — header-seek\n"
              "    clicks and velocity-lane clicks did not reclaim it. Now any click on\n"
              "    the editor canvas, waveform strip, or velocity lane reclaims focus\n"
              "    automatically.\n"
              "  - MIDI Editor: playhead now stays in sync with what you hear. The\n"
              "    visual playhead used to run 30-80 ms ahead of audio because the\n"
              "    audio output buffer + OS audio path took time to flush after\n"
              "    pygame.mixer.music.play() returned. A new 'Audio output latency'\n"
              "    slider compensates for this — it is auto-estimated per OS at\n"
              "    startup (Windows ~42 ms / macOS ~22 ms / Linux ~37 ms) and\n"
              "    can be fine-tuned 0-200 ms if your hardware chain (Bluetooth,\n"
              "    HDMI, USB DAC) drifts in either direction. Same compensation also\n"
              "    fixes T-tap accuracy and the saved-position-on-pause behavior.\n"
              "  - MIDI Editor: when you tap T to mark the offset during playback,\n"
              "    the captured timestamp now reflects the audio position you heard,\n"
              "    not where the playhead overshot to.")

